data.title: Great Find
data.text: We tried this place twice already. It is not a fancy, but clean and spacious with enough tables and sitting areas to have a quick lunch. We sat in the back and watched the trains go by as we ate.  For us, the empanadas are quite filling. The first time, we ordered two each and two dessert to share. It was way too much food for us, so second time we only ordered one empanada per person. We tried the #1 Chicken, #2 Beef, #10 Pork Chile Verde, #11 Beef Pot Roast and desserts #1D Guava and #2D Cinnamon Apple. We recommend this place and plan on going back.

data.title: Tasty Empanadas, well done!
data.text:
New to Mission Viejo, we're trying to find the unique, local restaurants that our new city has to offer. This is a quick-serve restaurant. You order at the counter and then your order will be served at your table. There is a large display case that has the empanadas on view. The pastry was wonderfully flaky, the empanadas are served piping hot, and there is enough variety to please any eating style (meat eaters, vegetarians). I enjoyed the spinach and cheese as well as the green chili pork. Both were delicious! I will say that I thought it was a little pricey...$7 for two empanadas and a beverage (I did not get any sides), but that won't stop me from coming again. I'd like to try some different flavors. Oh, and what is so brilliant is that the server who brings your food will know automatically which empanadas are yours (if in a group) because the empanadas have a number baked into the corner of each one!! Brilliant!

I will say, and this is absolutely NO FAULT of the restaurant, but there is a High School directly across the street and MAN..when school lets out, the kids are all walking about, staring at their phones, nearly walking into cars, the parents are plugging up the entire parking lot with cars picking up their kids. It's too bad the parking lot cannot be monitored not to allow these parents in, it completely overwhelms the businesses who have the misfortune to be in this particular location. Come to eat when there is no fear of school letting out!! :-(

data.title: IS THIS ARGENTINA? NO, THIS IS MISSION VIEJO.
data.text: I was hosting an Argentinian parriada/asado/beef carnivore extravaganza. I didn't have the time or inclination to make my own empanadas, those flaky dough filled pastries of savory delights. The Maker to the rescue. Traditional beef, spinach and cheese and chicken. Other choices are at the whim of The Maker in the kitchen.  The chimmichuri and red sauce sides are terrific and accompany grilled red meats perfectly. Since I make almost everything myself, my guests asked me if i made the empanadas. In all honesty I had to give praise to and tip my hat to The  Empanada Maker.

data.title: Good for quick stop
data.text: This is a fast food empanadas place. They were edible and had a lot to choose from, but really tough to like when villa Romas is down the street.

data.title: Something different
data.text: This place is good if you are looking for something different, we love empanadas, and we enjoyed all different kind that they offer.

data.title: Best party decision ever!!
data.text: We ordered a bunch of breakfast empanadas for Christmas morning! They were awesome and everyone enjoyed them.   Bacon was a hit. I liked the spinach ones.  I ordered a bunch of the mixed specialty dinner ones for a group of 15 the following weekend.  Turkey dinner, pot roast......etc - all great!!!! I spend the same amount ordering Pizza etc at the Tap House.  This was a great change of pace and we will use them often!  Most men ate 3-4, gals ate 2-3.    Made great leftovers too.  Dessert ones were great too! Berry Cheese cake and apple!  Pumpkin pie was awesome too!

data.title: You won't miss here
data.text:
They experiment on a few items but they are all good. One of my favorite dessert is the guava/cheese.  Their sauce are great -  favorite is the chimichurri.  Price start @$2
I am surprised that it has not gotten more reviews here ( Yelp has

data.title: Amazing Diamon in the Rough
data.text: You would never think that such an amazing little restaurant would be hidden in an obsolete Mission Viejo strip mall, right before a highway 5 freeway on-ramp, but it's true.  The Empanada Maker blew me away.  My Cuban wife discovered it first and tried to get me to go for lunch but all I had had empanadas was before and they were a little pastry snack -- not a meal.  I reluctantly agreed to go.  Once I walked in, experienced the great atmosphere, friendly/helpful staff and myriad of choices, I was hooked.  I ordered the Chicken Florentine empanada (lightly breaded chicken breast, spinach, onions, sundried tomatoes, artichoke hearts, cream sauce and mozzarella cheese) and the Chocolate Creme Brulee empanada (a mix of chocolate custard and delicious creme brulee, chilled, for dessert.  I was absolutely amazed!  Great food. Great atmosphere.  Great service.  And a great experience!  FIVE STARS from me!

data.title: Empanadas en California
data.text: De pasada compramos un par de empanadas y nos gustaron, más que fue después de varias semanas lejos de casa. Estaban bien.

data.title: Super Empanada
data.text: C'est la première fois que nous avons essayé les Empanada et ils sont très bons. Il y a beaucoup de choix (végétariens ou avec de la viande). Il y a même des Empanada pour le dessert. A manger sur place ou à emporter. Très bon rapport qualité prix.
